    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the DB metrics and they look okayish, like there's some latency but nothing that looks like a total outage or a massive spike. the \"unexpected token in JSON\" error is also weird because the payload we send is strictly validated before it even hits the service. \n\nit almost feels like the error is just popping in and out of existence. is there anything else that could cause this kind of erratic behavior that wouldn't show up clearly in the standard resource metrics?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Erratic behavior, especially when the database seems stable, often points to race conditions or external dependencies behaving unpredictably. It's possible a rogue, poorly-behaved third-party service is intermittently failing or returning malformed data that your JSON parser is choking on. You might need to implement more granular tracing around the entire checkout flow, not just the database interaction. Look closely at any external payment gateways or inventory services your checkout calls.",
      "source": "target",
